.TH EXAMPLE\-SENDER\-PY 1 "May 2026" "mu2e\-daq\-alert 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
example\-sender\-py \- send a Mu2e DAQ alert using the Python library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B example\-sender\-py
[\fB\-s\fR \fIID\fR]
[\fB\-m\fR \fITEXT\fR]
[\fB\-i\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fINUM\fR]
[\fB\-h\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B example\-sender\-py
constructs a JSON alert payload and broadcasts it as a single UDP datagram.
It is a minimal demonstration of the
.B daq_alert
Python package, specifically the
.B send_alert()
function.
.PP
The payload format is:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
{"system_id":"...","timestamp":"<ISO\-8601>","message":"..."}
.fi
.RE
.PP
The timestamp is generated automatically at the time of the call.
.PP
The script requires the
.B daq_alert
package to be importable.  Install it with
.B pip install libs/python/
or via the CMake install target before running.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system\-id " " \fIID\fR
Identifier of the sending system.
.br
Default: \fBDAQ\-NODE\-01\fR
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fITEXT\fR
Human\-readable alert message.
.br
Default: \fBTest alert from example\-sender\-py\fR
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ip " " \fIADDRESS\fR
UDP broadcast destination address.
.br
Default: \fB255.255.255.255\fR
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fINUM\fR
UDP destination port (1\(en65535).
.br
Default: \fB37020\fR
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Send an alert with default parameters:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
example\-sender\-py
.fi
.RE
.PP
Send an alert to a specific subnet with a custom system ID and message:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
example\-sender\-py \-\-system\-id DAQ\-NODE\-03 \e
    \-\-message "Readout buffer overflow" \e
    \-\-ip 192.168.1.255
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Alert sent successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid argument, missing dependency, or send failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR example\-sender\-c (1),
.BR example\-sender\-cpp (1)
